'''P. Frank Winkler, Jr.''' is an astronomer and noted [[subject-matter expert]] on [[supernova]]. He received his doctorate from Harvard and is currently the [[Gamaliel Painter]] Bicentennial Professor in Physics at [[Middlebury College]] located in Middlebury, [[Vermont]].<ref>[http://www.middlebury.edu/academics/physics/faculty/fwinkler Frank Winkler], Middlebury College</ref>
Dr. Winkler has calculated the distance for the brightest supernova event recorded in human history, [[SN 1006]], as being ~7,200 light years distant.
Winkler is also the recipient of record for a [[Recovery Act]] grant for continued research regarding supernova. Frank Winkler is also a member of the [[International Astronomical Union]].
