'''Harold Kosoff''' (November 5, 1930 &ndash; March 12, 1995) was an [[inventor]]. He is [[Inventor (patent)|credited]] with inventing the [[Reciprocating engine|free piston engine]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=RbIkAQAAMAAJ&q=%22Harold+Kosoff%22&dq=%22Harold+Kosoff%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwigiLjHzcvcAhWF44MKHSREAxAQ6AEISTAI|title=Technology and Urban Transportation: Environmental Quality Considerations|last=Ayres|first=Robert U.|last2=McKenna|first2=Richard P.|date=1968|publisher=Hudson Institute|language=en}}</ref> and the [[Battery (electricity)|battery-powered]] baby swing. [http://www.patentstorm.us/patents/4448410/fulltext.html U.S. Pat. No. 4,448,410] Exclusive rights for the battery-powered baby swing were sold to [[Graco (baby products)|Graco]]. In addition, Kosoff invented a [[Air cleaner|home air cleaner]] and [[chainless bicycle]] using an arc and pulley system.

