'''Johann Jacob Bremi-Wolf''' (25 May 1791, [[D√ºbendorf]] ‚Äì 27 February 1857, [[Z√ºrich]]) was a [[Switzerland|Swiss]] [[entomologist]] and ''Kunsthandwerker'' (art [[Turning|turner]]) in Z√ºrich.<ref>Guyet, E. V., 1974 ''Vom Naturalienkabinett der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft in Z√ºrich zum Zoologischen Museum der Universit√§t Vierteljahrsschrift der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft in Z√ºrich, Z√ºrich'' 119, S. 379, pp. 376-381, Schr.verz.</ref> He was deaf due to illness at the age of 11. His entomological [[herbarium]] is held by the [[Museum Wiesbaden]]. Other parts of his insect collection, especially [[Diptera]] are held by the [[:de:Naturforschende Gesellschaft in Z√ºrich|Naturforschende Gesellschaft in Z√ºrich]].

